			<h2><a href="http://sugarcrafter.net/2009/06/12/lemonade-cheesecake-pie/" rel="bookmark" title="Permanent Link to Lemonade Cheesecake Pie">Lemonade Cheesecake Pie</a></h2>

			<p class="post-info"><span class="date">June 12, 2009</span> | <a href="http://sugarcrafter.net/2009/06/12/lemonade-cheesecake-pie/print/" title="Print" rel="nofollow">Print</a>
 | <a href="http://sugarcrafter.net/2009/06/12/lemonade-cheesecake-pie/email/" title="E-mail" rel="nofollow">E-mail</a>
 | Filed under  <a href="http://sugarcrafter.net/tag/cheesecake/" rel="tag">cheesecake</a>, <a href="http://sugarcrafter.net/tag/lemon/" rel="tag">lemon</a>, <a href="http://sugarcrafter.net/tag/pie/" rel="tag">pie</a></p>

				
			<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3618360164" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 9" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3654/3618360164_2869916872.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>I&#8217;ve been feeling guilty because it&#8217;s been several days since I&#8217;ve posted an actual recipe, so I wanted to leave you with this easy pie recipe for the weekend. It&#8217;s a perfect summer dessert: cool, creamy, and light &#8211; and no baking is required!</p>
<p>Here&#8217;s what you&#8217;ll need:</p>
<p><strong>For the crust: </strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1 and 1/4 cup vanilla cookie crumbs</li>
<li>4 Tbsp butter, melted</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>For the filling:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>1 package (8oz) cream cheese</li>
<li>2 and 1/2 Tbsp sugar</li>
<li>1/2 cup milk</li>
<li>1/4 cup lemonade mix</li>
<li>2 cups Cool Whip/generic brand whipped topping</li>
</ul>
<p>First, throw the cookies in your food processor and grind them up. I only had about a cup&#8217;s worth, which I was able to get away with &#8211; but it&#8217;s better to have 1/4-1/2 cup more than that, depending on how thick you like your crust.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617539195/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 1" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3558/3617539195_57ff10907d.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Melt the butter, and then mix it in with the cookie crumbs until the mixture is moist and crumbly. Press it into the pie pan, and then stick the pan in the freezer to allow the crust to firm up a bit while we make the filling.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617538525/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 2" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2480/3617538525_8e15127af8.jpg?v=0" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Soften the cream cheese, and then add in the sugar, lemonade mix, and milk. Mix on medium speed until well-blended.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617537713/" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 3" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2466/3617537713_75276a5974.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Now, add in the Cool Whip. Don&#8217;t use the mixer here, just gently stir it into the mixture.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a style="text-decoration: none;" href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617537131" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 4" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3599/3617537131_cdcf4b07ee.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3618356012" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 5" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3661/3618356012_c91b5dd7d9.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Grab the pie crust out of the freezer, and pour the filling into it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617536077" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 6" src="http://farm3.static.flickr.com/2425/3617536077_fe84b20b6d.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Smooth it out&#8230;and then stick it in the fridge for about an hour. I know, it&#8217;s hard, but it&#8217;ll be worth it.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617536581" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 7" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3354/3617536581_e1d0ae52f1.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>When the hour is up, add a topping! You can choose anything from lemon slices, to berries, to some kind of citrus sauce&#8230;me, I like lemon zest.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617541383" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 8" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3302/3617541383_e8c1e1e76c.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Oh, yeah. I love my new zester.</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3618360164" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie - 9" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3654/3618360164_2869916872.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<p>Cut yourself a slice, sit back, and relax. It practically melts in your mouth!</p>
<p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://www.flickr.com/photos/technically_tracy/3617540613" onclick="javascript:_gaq.push(['_trackEvent','outbound-article','www.flickr.com']);"><img class="aligncenter" title="Lemonade Cheesecake Pie" src="http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3629/3617540613_8b5b966066.jpg" alt="" width="500" height="333" /></a></p>
<div class="shr-publisher-1122"></div> <div class="linkwithin_div"></div>

	
		
